        "title": "Add development trace UI",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a source-checkout-only development LLM trace recorder for full prompt/tool payload debugging.\n- Exposes `traces.capabilities`, `traces.list`, and `traces.get` Gateway methods behind explicit development flags, admin scope, and a strict direct-loopback browser Control UI grant.\n- Adds a Traces Control UI view with list/detail panes, prompt/tool/parameter/response JSON sections, i18n strings, docs, changelog, and mocked Gateway E2E coverage.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/llm-dev-tracing.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/traces.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.ui-e2e.config.ts --configLoader runner ui/src/ui/e2e/traces.e2e.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --prompt 'Review the OpenClaw development LLM tracing UI implementation only. Ignore unrelated untracked docs/refactor/*.md files that were already present in the workspace.'`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Development-only tracing UI shows captured LLM prompt payloads and tool schemas while remaining disabled outside an explicit source-checkout loopback debugging session.\n\nReal environment tested: Local Control UI Playwright/Chromium E2E server with mocked Gateway WebSocket responses, using the repo's Control UI E2E helper.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Captured a Playwright browser recording through the Traces route with `OPENCLAW` mock trace capability enabled, then ran the committed trace E2E test command above.\n\nEvidence after fix: Recording captured at local artifact `.artifacts/control-ui-traces-recording/page@94f23dd98457c423703da5d470588997.webm`; screenshot captured at `.artifacts/control-ui-traces-recording/tracing-ui.png`; the script asserted the Traces sidebar item, detail header, full prompt text, tool schema, and non-overlapping list/detail panes.\n\nObserved result after fix: The Traces tab rendered the selected `openai/gpt-5.5` trace, displayed the full prompt payload and `shell_exec` tool schema, and hid the tab when `traces.capabilities.available` was false in the committed E2E test.\n\nWhat was not tested: A live provider request with real credentials; the proof intentionally uses deterministic mocked Gateway data to avoid recording real prompts or secrets.",
